**Rental yield** measures the annual rent as a percentage of the property value. Gross yield = (Annual Rent / Property Value) × 100. Net yield deducts maintenance, property tax, vacancy periods, and brokerage. Indian residential property typically yields 2–3.5% — lower than FD returns — which is why property investment is often more capital appreciation than income play.
